CONTINENTAL OVERVIEW
Warfare in 1308 AF operates without gunpowder. The dominant technologies are iron and steel weapons, heavy cavalry, naval vessels, siege engines, and the tactical doctrines of four centuries of post-imperial state formation. The imperial road network — maintained by the Brothers of the Open Road — functions simultaneously as trade infrastructure and military logistics. Whoever feeds their army through the roads fastest usually wins. Every major region's military reflects its terrain, its economy, and the specific trauma that formed it.

