PART THREE: TRADE ROUTES AND ECONOMICS

THE MAJOR NAMED TRADE ROUTES
The Inner Sea Necklace Maritime loop: Nionia → Westhorn (Horns) → Brinehold → Nightspike → Red Coast Porto Rubia → Teeth → Nionia. The continent's primary naval commercial circuit. Carries: marble, iron tools, salt cod, volcanic stone, spices, featherwork, copper goods, medicinal compounds.
The Great Grainway Overland: Vornhold → Beaumont Forest → Horns junction → western cities. The continent's food supply line. Controlled by Silverblood at the eastern end. Beaumont charges passage in the middle. Garrun takes toll at the Horns junction. The most contested route on the continent.
The Copper Road Red Coast → Vallan passes → Heartlands manufacturing centers. Raw and worked copper moving northwest. Silver, iron goods, and grain moving southeast. Passes through Vallan toll stations. Vallan's primary road-tax income source.
The Silver Road Heartlands → Sangrean border via southern mountain passes. Silver and silver goods moving south. Sangrean wine, spice, and luxury goods moving north. Competes with river routes for merchant preference.
The Jungle Road Sangrea (Muroverde gateway) → Xaria. The most dangerous land route on the continent. Perhaps a hundred caravans per year. Carries cacao, jade, featherwork, exotic hardwoods, vanilla, medicinal plants north. Returns grain, tools, cloth, metalwork south.
The Vallan Corridor Mainland → Teeth and Isle of Knowledge via Hortakin passes. The safest overland route on the continent. Preferred for high-value, low-weight trade: alchemical supplies, books, fine instruments, scholarly correspondence.
The Deadwood Track Heartlands (Corvallis territory) → Frozen South. Currently irregular; controlled effectively by Corbeau and Silverring. Carries Frozen South gold south; returns mainland steel and grain north. The route that is breaking the Whaletooth Compact.
The Fjord Lane Frozen South coastal maritime route; connects the coastal clans internally. Carries gold, furs, and whale products. Not used by mainland merchants — conditions make it fatal without local knowledge.
The Teeth Bridge Route The Great Bridge. Continental connector between the northern and southern halves. Currently strangled by Morvayn's tolls. Everything passes through it; the toll revenue makes Morvayn wealthy.
The Pilgrims' Road Multiple routes converging on Faithir. Enormous commercial traffic follows the pilgrims. Brothers of the Open Road maintain it. The Church's economic lifeblood.
The Obsidian Path Red Coast (Khorim) → Vallan → Heartlands. Khorim obsidian, alchemical instruments, Red Coast spices moving inland. Iron tools and grain returning.
The Ice-Shore Road Coastal Rosland → Frozen South (overland and maritime hybrid). Roslandic iron tools and grain going south; Frozen South gold dust and fur going north. Operated by House Zelnik's fishing fleet.

