Crown-Viper — Shadowtide and deep Selvaverde canopy; iridescent scales; hallucinogenic bite; two to three days of vivid visions, then death if untreated
Ember-Lizard — Emberstone volcanic gecko; bioluminescent spots; heat-adapted; extremely fast; miners swear they predict eruptions
Reef-Serpent — Singing Reef; large non-venomous sea snake; up to twelve feet; feeds on fish; often mistaken for something more dangerous
Mud-Eel — Shadowtide Rootsea; large; produces electric charge; the primary reason watermen use poles rather than reaching into the water
Rootsea-Creature — Shadowtide deep channels; large water displacement; never fully observed; accepts offerings from the Duskwalkers; the island's deepest secret

XARIA
Selvaverde-Jaguar — jungle apex predator; used in Xarian military psychological warfare; the Ya'ax warriors' patron animal
Caiman — large freshwater crocodilian; Ix'za delta; sacred to Ixchela; semi-tolerated in canal city spaces; genuinely dangerous
Quetzal — the most prized featherwork bird; green and red; approaching practical extinction due to feather-trade demand; Kuk'ul guild attempts to regulate harvest
River-Dolphin — pink freshwater dolphin; Ix'za river; sacred; killing one requires full ritual purification; fishermen who accidentally kill them face social ostracism
Poison-Dart-Frog — multiple species; Cascabella primary venom source; also traded live to mainland alchemists
Ix'za-Iguana — large arboreal; sacred in Zari; kept in the Vizier's gardens; considered a minor river deity incarnation
Harpy-Eagle — massive jungle raptor; featherwork use; also used by House Hok'ul's ritual warriors for psychological warfare
Howler-Monkey — territorial; loud; Ya'ax warriors use monkey alarm calls as jungle early-warning systems for approaching enemies
Wild-Boar — feral; introduced during colonial era; now part of the jungle ecology; hunted as food

